          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Layers of thulium(III)oxide (Tm2O3)99.9%,"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "69-TM-169",
                "field_identifier": "NAT",
                "value": 1.0
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "EXTB",
                "EDEG",
                "GSPEC",
                "MOSEP",
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Thin layers of thulium(III)oxide (Tm2O3) were prepared",
                "using the sedimentation  technique onto 0.1 mm thick",
                "Al backing and covered by 0.01mm Al foil.",
                "The thickness of the sediment layer",
                "was about 10-20mg/cm2 Tm2O3 . Stacked-foil technique",
                "was used.  Irradiation was done at 45 MeV proton",
                "energy (100nA, 1 hour) at COSY cyclotron Juelich.",
                "Stack2 was irradiated at 36 MeV proton energy (150",
                "nA, 20min) at VUB cyclotron.",
                "Energy degradation in the stack was determined by",
                "the polynomial approximation of the stopping-power",
                "Andersen and Ziegler, 1977, corrected on the basis of",
                "the excitation function of the natTi(p,x)48V (VUB) and",
                "natCu(p,xn)62,63Zn (COSY)monitor reactions."
              ]
            }
          ],
